_raw.rds` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mk_raw.rds under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_7yTmhBUBce1FgIqN3nPm57l5", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use the `methRead` function from methylKit to read the Bismark coverage files located in the `input/` directory. Set the parameters as follows:\\n   - `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`\\n   - `mincov=4`\\n   - `treatment = c(0, 0, 0)`\\n   - `assembly = 'mock_v1'`\\n   - Use relative paths for the input files.\\n3. Save the resulting methylRawList object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n4. Verify that the file `output/mk_raw.rds` has been created.\\n5. Submit the task as done if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_load`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_load\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `early`, difficulty: `1`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this wor