ary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_7yTmhBUBce1FgIqN3nPm57l5", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use the `methRead` function from methylKit to read the Bismark coverage files located in the `input/` directory. Set the parameters as follows:\\n   - `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`\\n   - `mincov=4`\\n   - `treatment = c(0, 0, 0)`\\n   - `assembly = 'mock_v1'`\\n   - Use relative paths for the input files.\\n3. Save the resulting methylRawList object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n4. Verify that the file `output/mk_raw.rds` has been created.\\n5. Submit the task as done if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (527 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_7yTmhBUBce1FgIqN3nPm57l5"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_kphtlDkllqRQ1sg3Jv4wPeoW", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile_paths <- c('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov')\\n\\n# Read the methylation data\\nmethyl_data <- methRead(\\n  location = file_paths,\\n  pipeline = 'bismarkCoverage',\\n  mincov = 4,\\n  treatment = c(0, 0, 0),\\n  assembly = 'mock_v1'\\n)\\n\\n# Save the methylRawList object\\nsaveRD